# mobile-fills.log — mobile GE trades captured via the app's GitHub-as-backend quick-add (PLAN.md M1).
# Append-only SOURCE log. SAME line vocabulary as coffer-manual.log — BOUGHT / SOLD / WITHDRAWN /
# BANKED fill lines plus {"state":"REMOVE","target":"<eventId>"} tombstones — but written to SLOT 9
# (mobile) so its provenance stays distinct from desktop/CLI manual entries (slot 8) and live GE
# slots (0-7). The phone appends here directly via the GitHub contents API (js/github.js); the PC's
# sync-fills.mjs READS this file (it NEVER writes it — single-writer discipline) and folds the lines
# into fills.json / positions.json through the normal reconstruction. Comment lines (starting with #)
# are ignored by the parser. Do not hand-edit while the pipeline may run; append a REMOVE tombstone to
# correct a line (fills.json is an append-only archive — deleting a source line alone won't purge it).
